  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Basic legal definition:\n- Concealing the origins of illegally obtained money\n- Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate funds\n- Disguising the source, ownership, or destination of money\n\n2. Common legal components:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Proceeds from criminal activity\n- Attempting to make funds appear legitimate\n\n3. Typical stages:\n- Placement: Introducing illegal funds into financial system\n- Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions\n- Integration: Reintroducing funds as seemingly legitimate income\n\n4. Jurisdictional variations exist, but most definitions include:\n- Knowledge of funds' illegal origins\n- Intent to conceal criminal proceeds\n- Purposeful financial manipulation\n\n5. Examples of triggering activities:\n- Drug trafficking proceeds\n- Fraud earnings\n- Embezzlement\n- Illegal gambling income\n\nNote: Specific legal definitions can vary between countries and legal systems. This overview provides general information, not comprehensive legal advice.",
